description:
Alyssa Truman interviews Dwain Esmond, associate director of the Ellen G. White Estate, to uncover an inspiring story of Adventist education and a loving Christian influence.

The importance of intercession and mentorship in a life, especially that of a young person, cannot be overestimated. When we take the time to disciple and encourage others, we can make an eternal impact in their lives. Such was the case of Dwain Esmond who, throughout his youth, had others in the church support and nurture his spiritual growth. 

Listen in as he talks about the people who invested in him throughout his youth and young adult life and how he was able to find his purpose through their intercession.
